androidx.lifecycle

Interface LifecycleOwner

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    LifecycleRegistryOwner
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AmbientModeSupport, AppCompatActivity, AppCompatDialogFragment, BaseSupportFragment, BrandedSupportFragment, BrowseSupportFragment, CarDrawerActivity, ComponentActivity, DetailsSupportFragment, DialogFragment, EditTextPreferenceDialogFragmentCompat, ErrorSupportFragment, Fragment, FragmentActivity, GuidedStepSupportFragment, GuidedStepSupportFragment.DummyFragment, HeadersSupportFragment, LifecycleService, ListFragment, ListPreferenceDialogFragmentCompat, MediaRouteChooserDialogFragment, MediaRouteControllerDialogFragment, MediaRouteDiscoveryFragment, MultiSelectListPreferenceDialogFragmentCompat, OnboardingSupportFragment, PlaybackSupportFragment, PreferenceDialogFragmentCompat, PreferenceFragmentCompat, ProcessLifecycleOwner, RowsSupportFragment, SearchSupportFragment, VerticalGridSupportFragment, VideoSupportFragment

    public interface LifecycleOwner
    A class that has an Android lifecycle. These events can be used by custom components to handle lifecycle changes without implementing any code inside the Activity or the Fragment.

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
